1
00:00:01,418 --> 00:00:02,628
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:30,299 --> 00:01:36,221
UNRAVELING

3
00:01:40,017 --> 00:01:41,435
[all gasping]

4
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:43,687
[both] Huh?

5
00:01:44,855 --> 00:01:45,731
[all] Huh...

6
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:48,775
I am L.

7
00:01:49,234 --> 00:01:50,527
[Yagami] This is him?

8
00:01:50,861 --> 00:01:53,238
[Matsuda] Hmm.
He's nothing like I thought he'd be.

9
00:01:53,488 --> 00:01:54,573
Uh...

10
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:55,991
Hmm...

11
00:01:57,034 --> 00:01:58,785
I'm Yagami of the NPA.

12
00:01:59,578 --> 00:02:00,662
I'm Matsuda.

13
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:01,830
I'm Aizawa.

14
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:03,457
-Mogi.
-Ukita.

15
00:02:05,292 --> 00:02:06,710
I'm very sorry we're late.

16
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:08,545
Currently, the five of us are...

17
00:02:08,879 --> 00:02:09,921
Bang!

18
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,923
-Huh?
-What the hell was that?

19
00:02:12,215 --> 00:02:13,216
Hmm.

20
00:02:13,675 --> 00:02:16,845
If I were Kira you would be dead,
Mr. Soichiro Yagami,

21
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:18,013
Chief of the NPA.

22
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:18,972
[all exclaiming]

23
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:22,601
Kira needs a face and a name
in order to commit murder,

24
00:02:22,809 --> 00:02:25,562
but I'm sure you've already figured
that much out, haven't you?

25
00:02:26,313 --> 00:02:29,066
Please do not give out
your names so carelessly.

26
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:30,651
Instead...

27
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:32,903
let's value our lives.

28
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:35,113
I knew that he needed a face
to kill someone,

29
00:02:35,197 --> 00:02:38,241
but I don't remember any evidence
that showed that he needed a name too.

30
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:41,203
There's no way to verify
if this is related to criminals

31
00:02:41,286 --> 00:02:43,121
whose names were never released publicly

32
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:46,958
or whose names were spelled incorrectly
in the media have not been targeted.

33
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:49,586
We briefly went over it
at one of our meetings.

34
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:52,839
[L] That's enough small talk for now.
Come this way.

35
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:54,424
Oh, right.

36
00:02:54,675 --> 00:02:56,802
[L] Please turn off
all your cellphones, handhelds,

37
00:02:56,927 --> 00:02:58,804
and any other communication devices

38
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:00,639
and leave them on the table right there.

39
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:05,060
What? Do you think we're going to be
using our cellphones during this meeting

40
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:06,311
to leak information?

41
00:03:06,395 --> 00:03:08,105
It's all right. Just do as he says.

42
00:03:09,815 --> 00:03:12,192
[Matsuda] I realize he's been cautious
from the very beginning,

43
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:14,277
but I still can't tell
if he trusts us or not.

44
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,238
[L] No, I just find them distracting.

45
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:20,117
I can't stand it when people's cellphones
are ringing while I'm trying to talk.

46
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:25,247
Let me start by saying nobody takes notes
on anything that's said in these meetings.

47
00:03:25,414 --> 00:03:27,999
That means, when we leave Headquarters,
any information we need

48
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:29,251
is committed to memory.

49
00:03:30,669 --> 00:03:32,462
Please, make yourselves comfortable.

50
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:34,506
[grunts] Right.

51
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:46,351
[sips loudly]

52
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:50,355
[gulps loudly]

53
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:51,857
[groans]

54
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:57,696
-Excuse me, L?
-[L] Hmm.

55
00:03:57,821 --> 00:04:00,615
And from now on, I'll have to ask
that you stop calling me "L."

56
00:04:00,741 --> 00:04:02,576
It's "Ryuzaki" now, just to be safe.

57
00:04:03,201 --> 00:04:05,370
Uh, okay, Ryuzaki...

58
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:08,373
if we know that he needs
a name and a face to kill,

59
00:04:08,457 --> 00:04:10,250
couldn't we cut down on
the number of victims

60
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,169
by keeping criminals' names from the news?

61
00:04:12,711 --> 00:04:15,505
If we do that, we'll only be putting
the general public at risk.

62
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:17,799
-The general public?
-Why?

63
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,637
Kira is childish and he hates losing.

64
00:04:23,013 --> 00:04:24,097
But how do you...?

65
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:25,515
Just what do you mean?

66
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:27,142
Well...

67
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:29,478
I'm also childish and I hate to lose.

68
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,188
That's how I know.

69
00:04:32,481 --> 00:04:33,482
Ryuzaki…

70
00:04:34,024 --> 00:04:36,526
Would you mind being
a little more specific for us?

71
00:04:37,486 --> 00:04:38,862
Early on in the investigation,

72
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,406
I tried to provoke Kira
with that broadcast.

73
00:04:42,574 --> 00:04:45,494
[L] Up until then, we thought
that Kira would only go after criminals.

74
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:49,664
But as we all witnessed,
he didn't hesitate to kill my stand-in.

75
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:53,376
Also, as soon as I said we knew
he was in the Kanto region,

76
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:57,047
in defiance, he made sure his next victims
came from within Japan,

77
00:04:57,172 --> 00:04:59,841
as if to say,
"What are you gonna do about it?"

78
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,176
[slurps]

79
00:05:02,511 --> 00:05:04,346
He's met each of my challenges head on

80
00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:07,098
and he's never missed an opportunity
to return the favor.

81
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:09,267
Now, what do you think would happen

82
00:05:09,351 --> 00:05:13,355
if we tried to use media restrictions
to hide criminals from someone like that?

83
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:14,815
I guess...

84
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:18,443
"If you choose to withhold the names
of your worst criminals,

85
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:20,862
I'll kill petty criminals or the innocent.

86
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:23,990
I'm holding the whole world hostage,
so who's it gonna be?

87
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:26,493
I'm not the evil one here.

88
00:05:26,618 --> 00:05:30,831
But all those who oppose me
by hiding criminals, you are truly evil."

89
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:32,874
[L sighs]

90
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:35,377
That's exactly how Kira thinks.

91
00:05:35,544 --> 00:05:39,005
In any case, let's look at another way
we can use the media to draw him out.

92
00:05:39,631 --> 00:05:40,799
But how?

93
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:42,759
How about something like this?

94
00:05:43,844 --> 00:05:46,638
"Death of FBI agents infuriates the U.S.

95
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:49,641
Latest killings anger
the international policing community.

96
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:52,686
Nations agree to send 1,500 investigators
to Japan."

97
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:56,815
For Kira, this will be way beyond
what he faced with the FBI.

98
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:59,609
He'll see everyone as a potential threat.

99
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:02,070
Psychologically,
he'll start to feel cornered,

100
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:04,948
and that will cause him
to take some kind of drastic action.

101
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,033
T-- That's interesting.

102
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:11,288
So he'll think there are 1,500,
when there really are only seven of us.

103
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:13,748
And since none
of these investigators exist,

104
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:15,333
Kira won't be able to kill them.

105
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,626
It just might work!

106
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:19,045
Well, before we celebrate,

107
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:21,756
I'll tell you the rest of my thoughts
on the Kira case.

108
00:06:22,007 --> 00:06:23,425
[all grunting]

109
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:25,594
Kira works alone.

110
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:29,097
He had access
to all our classified information.

111
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:32,309
What evidence do you have
that he's working alone?

112
00:06:32,434 --> 00:06:33,393
Hold on, Aizawa.

113
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:36,354
Let's listen to his entire theory
before asking questions.

114
00:06:37,272 --> 00:06:39,733
We know he needs
a name and a face to kill.

115
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:43,069
And, to some extent,
he can control a victim's' time of death

116
00:06:43,153 --> 00:06:45,030
and their actions before dying.

117
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:49,075
[L] We already know that much.
Please keep that in mind...

118
00:06:49,868 --> 00:06:52,203
and listen carefully
to what I have to say next.

119
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:57,709
On December 14,
twelve FBI investigators entered Japan.

120
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:00,003
ENTER JAPAN

121
00:07:00,712 --> 00:07:02,505
And here we are on December 19…

122
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:06,092
Using prison inmates,
Kira conducts experiments,

123
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:08,720
manipulating his victims' actions
before they die.

124
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,460
12/19 TEST
12/14 FBI (12) ENTER JAPAN

125
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,310
In other words, during this window
of only five days,

126
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:14,643
Kira became aware of the FBI's presence

127
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:16,478
and obviously felt threatened.

128
00:07:17,354 --> 00:07:19,481
Because he didn't know
any of their names or faces,

129
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:21,191
he was at a disadvantage.

130
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:24,569
He needed to know how much control
he had over his victims

131
00:07:24,653 --> 00:07:26,696
before he could use it
against the twelve agents.

132
00:07:27,197 --> 00:07:29,658
And as we all know, on December 27…

133
00:07:30,909 --> 00:07:34,287
[Light] I got a hold of a file
which contained all the names and faces

134
00:07:34,371 --> 00:07:36,998
of the FBI investigators in Japan,

135
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:40,001
and I succeeded
in killing each one of them.

136
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:44,130
It's practically impossible to guess
which agent gave the file to Kira.

137
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:48,009
But I have to make sure
that no one ever finds out

138
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,387
that I came into contact with Raye Penber.

139
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,555
12/20 BUS

140
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:57,185
Huh? How come you're not using
the Death Note today?

141
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:59,270
You studying for those entrance exams?

142
00:07:59,646 --> 00:08:02,816
Those are the least of my worries.
Plus, it's a little late to start now.

143
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,985
Oh? Whatcha doing?

144
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,821
December 19 to December 27...

145
00:08:08,196 --> 00:08:10,573
I've been most active during this period.

146
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:13,368
During this period,
to the best of our knowledge,

147
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:16,538
at least twenty-three individuals
died of heart attacks.

148
00:08:17,414 --> 00:08:20,625
But these victims were different
from Kira's previous targets.

149
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:23,211
They were all alleged criminals,
ex-convicts,

150
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:25,213
or suspects in ongoing investigations.

151
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:27,132
So, legally speaking, they were innocent.

152
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:28,550
That's true.

153
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:32,887
What this indicates is that Kira had
to manipulate these lesser criminals

154
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:35,098
in order to kill those FBI agents.

155
00:08:35,724 --> 00:08:38,852
He killed that many people
so we'd be unable to tell the decoys

156
00:08:38,935 --> 00:08:40,562
from those who were actually used.

157
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:43,481
In truth, he probably only needed a few.

158
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:45,734
He waited eight days

159
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:48,153
so the FBI could investigate
other suspects,

160
00:08:48,278 --> 00:08:51,114
which meant there'd be no timeline
linking him to their deaths.

161
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:55,535
I suspect Kira had to be one of the people
being investigated by the FBI,

162
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:58,705
between the 14th and the 19th of December.

163
00:08:59,122 --> 00:09:00,582
In fact, I have no doubt.

164
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:02,751
[all gasping]

165
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:05,336
These are files provided by the FBI.

166
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:08,423
And they contain additional information
you might find useful.

167
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:11,634
For obvious reasons, you're not permitted
to take these out of this room.

168
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,761
-But...
-[Matsuda] Amazing!

169
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:14,512
There might only be five of us,

170
00:09:14,596 --> 00:09:15,889
but with this much information,

171
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,849
we should be able to cover
a lot of ground.

172
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:20,477
[Aizawa] We'll split into two teams.
One team traces the FBI agents,

173
00:09:20,602 --> 00:09:22,562
the other looks at
the heart attack victims.

174
00:09:22,896 --> 00:09:24,647
There weren't that many people
who had access

175
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:26,107
to information from headquarters.

176
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:30,320
And of those, the FBI only investigated
a small group in the first five days.

177
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:31,404
Yeah. Yeah...

178
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:34,324
So, does anyone have any questions?

179
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:35,658
Huh?

180
00:09:35,784 --> 00:09:37,077
[Yagami] Actually, Ryuzaki,

181
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:38,953
I do have one question for you.

182
00:09:39,788 --> 00:09:42,832
And it pertains to what you said
to us earlier about how you hate to lose.

183
00:09:42,957 --> 00:09:45,627
Does the fact that you've shown us
your face mean that you've lost?

184
00:09:45,752 --> 00:09:48,254
By just being here,
are you admitting defeat to Kira?

185
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,964
That's right.

186
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:51,800
By showing my face to you now

187
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:54,385
and by sacrificing the lives
of twelve FBI agents,

188
00:09:54,469 --> 00:09:55,887
I have lost the battle.

189
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:58,223
But I'm not going to lose the war.

190
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,684
This is the first time
I've ever put my life on the line.

191
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:05,063
I want to show Kira that we're all willing
to risk our lives,

192
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:06,439
if that's what it takes.

193
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:09,943
[chuckles] And that justice will prevail,
no matter what.

194
00:10:11,194 --> 00:10:12,445
Hey, yeah, that's right.

195
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:13,863
I like the sound of that.

196
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:15,073
We can do this!

197
00:10:15,198 --> 00:10:17,242
All right then. Let's do this, Ryuzaki.

198
00:10:17,659 --> 00:10:21,371
[Yagami] Well, I had my doubts
about whether it was really him at first,

199
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:23,039
but there's no mistaking it.

200
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:25,041
This man is L.

201
00:10:25,834 --> 00:10:29,712
Before we go any further, I have to be
absolutely sure that none of you are Kira.

202
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:32,841
So I'll need to speak with each of you
individually before you leave today.

203
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:34,425
Huh?

204
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:37,345
What's the deal?
He still doesn't trust us?

205
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:39,222
[Yagami]
No. I think it's a fair request.

206
00:10:39,514 --> 00:10:41,391
Try to see it from his perspective.

207
00:10:41,516 --> 00:10:43,726
Kira's been getting information
from our headquarters

208
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:45,019
from the very beginning.

209
00:10:45,103 --> 00:10:47,063
So there's a good chance
that he's one of us.

210
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:49,482
Chief's right. Working this case
has given us a chance

211
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:50,692
to see him in person.

212
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,986
He's risking his life to be here.

213
00:10:55,405 --> 00:10:56,906
[L] Things are going well.

214
00:10:57,115 --> 00:11:01,077
Just one clue, a single decisive factor,
is all I need.

215
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:03,663
[Light] Just one oversight...

216
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:07,041
A single piece of evidence
is all it would take.

217
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:10,086
It could cost me my life.

218
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:12,672
-Just one thing…
-Just one thing…

219
00:11:13,506 --> 00:11:17,844
[cars honking]

220
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:42,368
[birds chirping]

221
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:44,829
[Ryuk] You already finished studying?

222
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:46,372
I guess.

223
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:50,043
I'll be fine. I haven't missed anything.

224
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:53,630
The biggest risk I've taken so far
was that bus-jacking incident.

225
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:56,466
But they'll never be able
to connect it with Kira.

226
00:11:56,925 --> 00:12:00,345
Fortunately for me,
both the police and L don't know

227
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:03,473
that Kira can kill people by means
other than a heart attack.

228
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:06,976
However, if anyone were
to discover that fact,

229
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,436
I'd be in a lot of trouble.

230
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:11,105
What? Does it have to be now?

231
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:14,025
Your father's been pulling overnighters
with no change of clothes.

232
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:15,777
So you're going to bring this to him.

233
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:19,072
But, Mom, I totally promised my friends
that I'd go out with them today.

234
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,532
Why don't I go? I could use a break.

235
00:12:21,658 --> 00:12:22,659
Thanks, Light!

236
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:24,410
I owe you one next time.

237
00:12:25,245 --> 00:12:28,373
So, I guess this'll give you a chance
to spy on the police.

238
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,708
I won't go further
than the reception desk.

239
00:12:32,502 --> 00:12:34,754
[suspenseful music playing]

240
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:37,382
[Ryuk] Oh, you're bringing a page?

241
00:12:37,632 --> 00:12:38,800
Planning to kill someone?

242
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:42,637
No, but lately, I've been bringing
a page with me every time I go out.

243
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,888
Just in case.

244
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:51,062
[Naomi] That day…

245
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:53,731
Raye said that he was planning
to go to Shinjuku.

246
00:12:56,734 --> 00:13:00,405
That same day, four people died
of heart attacks in the Shinjuku area.

247
00:13:00,989 --> 00:13:02,448
And... there was the bus-jacking.

248
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:03,992
BUS-JACKER DIES
AFTER BEING HIT BY CAR

249
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:07,578
There's no way it was a coincidence.

250
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:13,543
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY
AND PUBLIC SAFETY COMMISSION

251
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:15,962
That's it!

252
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:17,797
Kira can kill in other ways.

253
00:13:17,964 --> 00:13:19,924
It doesn't have to be a heart attack.

254
00:13:21,217 --> 00:13:22,760
The mobile customer
you are trying to reach...

255
00:13:22,927 --> 00:13:24,595
That's unusual for Dad.

256
00:13:25,013 --> 00:13:26,222
[phone beeps]

257
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,851
[Light] I wonder if he's in a meeting
right now.

258
00:13:32,562 --> 00:13:33,730
[Naomi] Please.

259
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:37,108
I need to speak directly with someone
from the special investigation Task Force.

260
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:38,359
It's urgent.

261
00:13:38,443 --> 00:13:40,111
I'm sorry, ma'am, but I can't help you.

262
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:43,740
As I've told you already, there is no one
at Task Force headquarters right now.

263
00:13:44,365 --> 00:13:46,034
There's no one at Headquarters?

264
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,077
Dad's cell is turned off.

265
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:49,620
What's going on?

266
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:51,748
[Naomi] Can't you contact them somehow?

267
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:54,667
I have information
relating to the Kira investigation.

268
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:56,794
The Kira investigation?

269
00:13:59,422 --> 00:14:02,050
Look, I'll call Headquarters
one more time for you.

270
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,051
One moment.

271
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:06,763
Hi, I'm Detective Soichiro Yagami's son,
Light Yagami.

272
00:14:06,888 --> 00:14:09,849
I brought my father a change of clothes
but it doesn't look like he's in.

273
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:10,975
Can I leave them here?

274
00:14:11,351 --> 00:14:13,644
Sure. Hey,
I haven't seen you in a while, Light.

275
00:14:13,770 --> 00:14:15,855
Oh, I'm sorry. Uh...

276
00:14:16,022 --> 00:14:17,190
What? You don't remember?

277
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:20,485
You helped solve the insurance fraud
murder investigation sometime last year.

278
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:23,404
But, hey, no one remembers a receptionist,
do they?

279
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:25,948
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm terrible with faces.

280
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:28,242
I just need to sign my name
on this form, right?

281
00:14:28,743 --> 00:14:30,078
So, Light, does this mean

282
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:32,497
you're going to be helping us
with the Kira investigation too?

283
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:35,416
Sure, if all goes well,
maybe I'll find Kira before L does.

284
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:37,502
Find him before L does?

285
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,630
As I thought,
there's no one at Headquarters.

286
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,423
You're gonna have to trust me
on this, ma'am.

287
00:14:42,507 --> 00:14:45,343
I'll be sure to give them your message
as soon as I see them, I promise.

288
00:14:45,468 --> 00:14:48,012
[Naomi] That's not good enough.
I have to tell them in person.

289
00:14:48,137 --> 00:14:49,097
[Light] Excuse me.

290
00:14:49,389 --> 00:14:52,642
My father is actually in charge
of the Kira investigation.

291
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,894
If you'd like, I could pass your message
on to him?

292
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:58,689
His cellphone is off at the moment,
but I should be able to contact him soon.

293
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,818
A number of FBI agents were just killed.

294
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:05,238
And a lot of detectives have quit the case
because they're afraid of Kira.

295
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:07,240
So he's pretty busy right now.

296
00:15:07,365 --> 00:15:10,618
Uh, Light, it's probably better
if you don't discuss this with...

297
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:13,663
True, but it's practically
common knowledge at this point.

298
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:16,290
Besides, I feel like I can trust her.

299
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:18,418
You can almost see it in her eyes.

300
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:20,169
She's a wise and careful person.

301
00:15:21,129 --> 00:15:22,880
You heard about what happened

302
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:25,925
and you must have figured out
that the police had a leak of some kind.

303
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:28,928
And that's why you wanted
to tell them in person.

304
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:30,596
You thought this through.

305
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,140
Well, am I right?

306
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:33,641
[gasps]

307
00:15:35,852 --> 00:15:39,105
I'm sure my father will be calling me back
once he checks his messages.

308
00:15:39,230 --> 00:15:42,150
When he does, I'll give you the phone
and let you talk to him.

309
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:44,485
You sure that's all right?

310
00:15:44,819 --> 00:15:45,862
Oh, yeah.

311
00:15:45,987 --> 00:15:48,865
You understand why I can't just give you
my father's cellphone number,

312
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:51,909
but I have no problem letting you
use my phone to talk to him.

313
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:53,911
You'll have to trust my father and I,

314
00:15:53,995 --> 00:15:56,038
which I hope won't be
too difficult for you.

315
00:15:56,122 --> 00:15:57,748
[chuckles]

316
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:00,168
[Ryuk] Why is he so happy?

317
00:16:01,961 --> 00:16:03,212
Thank you so much.

318
00:16:03,713 --> 00:16:04,714
[chuckling]

319
00:16:04,922 --> 00:16:07,258
She walked right into that one,
didn't she?

320
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:13,014
I've gotta say,
you must be pretty brave

321
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:15,183
to be getting involved
in the Kira case like this.

322
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:16,851
[Naomi sighs] Not really.

323
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,853
[Light] So, according to you,
is Kira some...?

324
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:20,563
[clears throat]

325
00:16:21,189 --> 00:16:24,942
Um, we've been talking, and I just
realized I don't even know your name.

326
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:26,277
My name is Light Yagami.

327
00:16:27,028 --> 00:16:28,779
Light's written
with the character for "moon"

328
00:16:28,863 --> 00:16:31,282
and Yagami with the characters
for "night" and "god."

329
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:32,783
Kinda weird, huh?

330
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:34,577
My name's Shoko Maki.

331
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:36,579
It's written with the characters
for "shining."

332
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:38,372
"Ko" as in "child" and "ki" as in "tree."

333
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,374
Ms. Maki, right?

334
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,376
[Ryuk chuckles]

335
00:16:43,044 --> 00:16:44,212
[Light] Ms. Maki,

336
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:46,797
I've been thinking about Kira's powers.

337
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:49,759
And I believe they enable him
to somehow control his victims

338
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,052
before they die.

339
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:52,595
So do I!

340
00:16:52,929 --> 00:16:55,932
It's odd that you say that because
that's exactly what I've been thinking.

341
00:16:56,224 --> 00:16:58,935
Kira's able to control their actions
before he kills them.

342
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:00,394
But there's more to it.

343
00:17:00,478 --> 00:17:02,188
If my analysis so far is correct,

344
00:17:02,772 --> 00:17:06,067
Kira can kill in a number of ways,
not just with a heart attack.

345
00:17:07,527 --> 00:17:10,029
[Light] She knows? Who is this woman?

346
00:17:11,072 --> 00:17:13,407
I don't think anyone else knows this yet.

347
00:17:13,783 --> 00:17:15,952
But if the police
are willing to consider it,

348
00:17:16,077 --> 00:17:17,745
I bet it would help them catch Kira.

349
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:20,915
You know, that possibility
never even crossed my mind.

350
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:22,959
So, what you're saying is,

351
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:25,461
any time Kira wants one of his murders
to go undetected,

352
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:27,129
he wouldn't use a heart attack.

353
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:28,339
Right.

354
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:31,592
I'm almost positive that someone I know
may have met Kira.

355
00:17:31,801 --> 00:17:33,302
Met Kira?

356
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:34,929
[Light laughs]

357
00:17:35,096 --> 00:17:38,057
I'm sorry, but if a person came in
saying they'd met Kira,

358
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:41,102
the police would be more
than a little skeptical, to say the least.

359
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:42,603
[Naomi] I know.

360
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:46,274
That's why I need to explain it in person
to someone from Task Force headquarters.

361
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:48,317
Otherwise, I'm afraid
they'd just write me off.

362
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:51,445
But wouldn't it be better
if your friend spoke to them instead?

363
00:17:52,822 --> 00:17:55,032
He probably would,
but he's no longer alive.

364
00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:59,495
He was one of the twelve FBI agents
who came to Japan to investigate Kira.

365
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:04,375
An FBI agent who met Kira...

366
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:06,419
Could it be?

367
00:18:07,128 --> 00:18:09,130
[Naomi] You see, he was also my fiancé.

368
00:18:09,422 --> 00:18:11,757
While he was working, he got caught up
in a bus-jacking

369
00:18:11,841 --> 00:18:14,969
and I have reason to believe
that he met Kira on that bus.

370
00:18:16,846 --> 00:18:18,598
Raye Penber!

371
00:18:24,186 --> 00:18:25,438
Is something wrong?

372
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:28,983
Nothing. I'm sorry to hear
that he passed away.

373
00:18:31,402 --> 00:18:34,363
So... what makes you think
he met Kira on that bus?

374
00:18:36,032 --> 00:18:38,534
Because eight days
after that bus was hijacked...

375
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:42,496
he died, along with the other
FBI investigators.

376
00:18:43,122 --> 00:18:47,168
The same man had attempted to rob a bank
two days before he hijacked that bus.

377
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:50,004
And he dies in an accident?
Just like that?

378
00:18:50,504 --> 00:18:52,590
I mean, really, what are the odds?

379
00:18:54,717 --> 00:18:57,386
I've come to believe
that Kira set up that bus-jacking.

380
00:18:57,511 --> 00:19:00,514
It was planned to bring him
into contact with my fiancé,

381
00:19:00,890 --> 00:19:04,101
in order to obtain information regarding
the identities of the other FBI agents,

382
00:19:04,185 --> 00:19:05,770
so he could get rid of them all.

383
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:09,732
Anyway, what stands out to me
is that the hijacker died in an accident.

384
00:19:10,066 --> 00:19:11,150
In other words,

385
00:19:11,442 --> 00:19:14,737
it suggests that heart attacks
aren't the only way Kira can kill people.

386
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:29,627
[Light] Okay, so the bus-jacker
didn't die of a heart attack.

387
00:19:30,044 --> 00:19:33,589
And based on that, you're saying
Kira has other ways of killing people?

388
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:35,049
Yes.

389
00:19:35,341 --> 00:19:38,844
Don't take this the wrong way, but I think
that's a bit of a leap of faith.

390
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:41,472
There's no other way of looking at it.

391
00:19:41,639 --> 00:19:45,267
If Kira was controlling the hijacker,
chances are he killed him too.

392
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:47,186
[Light] I still don't see it.

393
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:48,854
I've been wondering about that bus-jacking

394
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:51,107
ever since my fiancé
first told me about it.

395
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:54,151
After he calmed down,
I asked him for details.

396
00:19:55,403 --> 00:19:57,738
He didn't mention any names
or anything like that,

397
00:19:57,822 --> 00:20:00,116
-but he told me one thing.
-[Light] What did he say?

398
00:20:00,825 --> 00:20:04,662
That he'd been put in a situation where
he had to show his FBI ID to someone.

399
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:08,916
Hmm?

400
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:13,045
The operation was undertaken secretly
without the NPA's knowledge.

401
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:15,172
He wasn't allowed to show his ID.

402
00:20:15,965 --> 00:20:18,509
I think, whoever saw his ID that day

403
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:21,095
was responsible for the deaths
of all of the agents.

404
00:20:21,971 --> 00:20:24,932
[Ryuk] Unbelievable. She figured it out.

405
00:20:25,099 --> 00:20:27,768
This must be the oversight
Light was worried about.

406
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,270
[Light] I understand.

407
00:20:29,395 --> 00:20:31,313
You're the only one who knows any of this.

408
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:33,566
And you want nothing more
than to avenge your fiancé

409
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:35,276
by bringing Kira to justice, right?

410
00:20:35,526 --> 00:20:38,863
And now you're convinced that Kira
can kill without using a heart attack?

411
00:20:39,113 --> 00:20:40,030
Yes.

412
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:43,826
[Light] There's no doubt in my mind
your deductive skills are excellent.

413
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:46,746
But you can't deny that you have
a personal interest in the case.

414
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:49,999
Still, your theory is worth looking into.

415
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,125
That's for sure.

416
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,794
Your testimony could be central
to the case.

417
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:55,129
It could.

418
00:20:56,005 --> 00:20:57,590
If what you're telling me is true,

419
00:20:57,715 --> 00:21:01,135
then it will only be a matter of time
before the police catch up with Kira.

420
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:05,389
The person your fiancé showed his ID to
on the bus that day...

421
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:07,808
it had to be Kira.

422
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,560
That's right.

423
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:17,359
[Light] That was close.

424
00:21:18,527 --> 00:21:19,820
This woman...

425
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:23,073
If she'd spoken to the police
before I met her...

426
00:21:23,741 --> 00:21:27,703
But it seems there's a god
on my side after all.

427
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,498
And not just a god of death.

428
00:21:38,267 --> 00:21:44,242
TO BE CONTINUED

429
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:54,605
[theme music plays]
